  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Weather forecasters today were offering drought-stricken farmers little prospect of relief in separate outlooks for the next 30 days and three months.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   A new climate assessment of the ongoing drought said "many areas now experiencing extreme drought have less than a 4 percent chance of recovering from the drought within 3 months".
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The disappointing forecast came as President Reagan headed to the Midwest to inspect drought-plagued farms.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The separate drought impact assessment, issued by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's Climate Office, points out that predicting an end to the drought is a complex thing, since dry spells have no normal lifetime.
  </a>
